We have the outcome of every single Superbowl in the NFL history, so we can find out which team performs the best in the 'clutch' (final stage of the playoffs).
In order to do that we have to determine the win rate of each team and find the most successful ones.

outputs.name: stdout
text: *for teams who appeared in no less than 5 superbowls

source:
print("We have the outcome of every single Superbowl in the NFL history, so we can find out which team performs the best in the 'clutch' (final stage of the playoffs).")
print("In order to do that we have to determine the win rate of each team and find the most successful ones.")
wins = pd.DataFrame(df['Winner'].value_counts()).reset_index().sort_values(['index']).reset_index().drop(['level_0'], axis=1).rename(columns = {'index' : 'Team'})
losses = pd.DataFrame(df['Loser'].value_counts()).reset_index().sort_values(['index']).reset_index().drop(['level_0'], axis=1).rename(columns = {'index' : 'Team'})
ratio = pd.merge(wins, losses, on='Team')
ratio['Appearences'] = ratio['Winner'] + ratio['Loser']
ratio = ratio.query('Appearences >= 4')  #we consider teams who reached the final at least 4 times to avoid useless stats (e.g team A appears in
                                         #the Superbowl once and wins it, therefore their win rate is 100% which doesn't represent their true success)
ratio['WPTG'] = ratio['Winner'] / ratio['Appearences'] #WPTG - Win percentage
ratio = ratio.sort_values(['WPTG'], ascending=True)
plt.xlim(0, 1)
plt.barh(ratio['Team'], ratio['WPTG'])
plt.xlabel('Win percentage')
plt.ylabel('Team')
plt.title('Win rates of Superbowl performers*')
plt.show()
print('*for teams who appeared in no less than 4 Superbowls')

From this analysis, we found out means, medians, standart deviations of points of winning and losing teams, as well as
marginal values. Also, we found stadiums which hosted the most Superbowls, these stadiums are Orange Bowl, Louisiana 
Superdome and Rose Bowl, all having hosted 5 events. This analysis provided margins of scores over the years. From the 
results one can see that graph doesnt show any patterns, except from random spikes, which says about unpredictibility
of the scores. New England Patriots and Pittsburgh Steelers have the most Superbowl titles - 6. New England Patriots 
and Denver Broncos have the most losses - 5. Tom Brady has the most MVPs - 4.
From the analysis of the Tom Brady case we can see that his finals teams have less than average margins of victory, 
which shows that he demonstrated his high ability in tougher situations, corresponding to the fact that he is one of
the best Superbowl performers. Also, we have introduced a way, evaluating the success of the performers, calculating
the best teams win shares. As a result, New York Giants and Green Bay Packers share the best win percentage - 80%, 
both teams have a record of 4-1 in the finals.
